<div type="definition">
<p>PRODUCE WRINKLES ON one's FOREHEAD AS A REACTION TO SOMETHING ONE has become AWARE of.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. Perhaps the most current word referring to all manner of frowning-like behaviour is pīn 顰 / 嚬.</p>
<p>2. Cù 蹙 refers specifically to the wrinkling of the nose.</p>
<p>NB: Zhòu 皺 refers specifically to the wrinkling of the forehead, but this usage is post-Han (TANG).</p>
        </div>
